00:28:09.754 --> 00:28:11.420
AUDIENCE: Less of a
technology question,

00:28:11.420 --> 00:28:15.010
but I was just curious where you
do the majority of your filming

00:28:15.010 --> 00:28:19.230
and how much is CGI versus how
much is actual physical sets?

00:28:19.230 --> 00:28:21.320
STEPHEN PETRANEK:
There's $15 million

00:28:21.320 --> 00:28:24.080
worth of sets in
Budapest right now.

00:28:24.080 --> 00:28:25.670
They're all packaged up.

00:28:25.670 --> 00:28:31.000
They were in a
container building,

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:34.000
as typical of Hollywood
sets, that you could have

00:28:34.000 --> 00:28:38.110
parked about seven 747s in.

00:28:38.110 --> 00:28:40.870
We built the largest
green screen ever

00:28:40.870 --> 00:28:44.590
in the history of movie making
so that we could go to Morocco

00:28:44.590 --> 00:28:49.360
and photograph where NASA rovers
are tested because it actually

00:28:49.360 --> 00:28:52.420
looks like and is a lot
like the surface of Mars.

00:28:52.420 --> 00:28:54.850
Then project that on the
screen and have the actors

00:28:54.850 --> 00:28:56.490
in front of that screen.

00:28:56.490 --> 00:28:59.390
It's kind of remarkable
stuff that they've done.

00:28:59.390 --> 00:29:00.940
They built full-size sets.

00:29:00.940 --> 00:29:04.090
For the first season when I
was walking through the sets,

00:29:04.090 --> 00:29:07.450
I mean, you really
can begin to think

00:29:07.450 --> 00:29:09.770
you're on Mars in
just a few minutes

00:29:09.770 --> 00:29:12.250
because things are so realistic.

00:29:12.250 --> 00:29:14.590
Down to there was
a little container

00:29:14.590 --> 00:29:18.200
in a hallway in the sets in
the first season on Mars.

00:29:18.200 --> 00:29:20.080
And I picked it up
and looked at it.

00:29:20.080 --> 00:29:22.420
And it was this container
that supposedly something

00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:24.040
had been brought to Mars in.

00:29:24.040 --> 00:29:26.650
And it had, like, six different
labels on it, you know,

00:29:26.650 --> 00:29:30.557
approved by inspector
such and such in Houston

00:29:30.557 --> 00:29:31.390
and stuff like that.

00:29:31.390 --> 00:29:35.340
I mean, down to the level that
